{"info": {"author": "Altertech", "author_email": "div@altertech.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: System :: Hardware", "Topic :: System :: Monitoring"], "description": "# Show pretty HDD/SSD list\n\nLong time ago when I've switched from Solaris to Linux, I missed \"hd\" utility.\nIn Linux \"hd\" command is used for a hex dump, in Solaris it displayed a pretty\ntable with HDD info.\n\nI wrote \"shd\" shell script with a similar functionality. Now I rewrote it in\nPython, added options and pretty colors, and releasing it to public.\n\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/alttch/shd/master/demo.gif\" />\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall *smartmontools*, then:\n\n```\npython3 -m pip install shd\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nTool should be started under root, to obtain S.M.A.R.T. info\n\n```\nshd [-h] [--temp-warn TEMP] [--temp-crit TEMP] [-R] [-y] [-e] [-s] [-J]\n\n  --temp-warn TEMP  Warning temperature, default: 40 C\n  --temp-crit TEMP  Critical temperature, default: 45 C\n  --fh, --fahrenheit  Temperature in Fahrenheit\n  -R, --raw         Suppress colors\n  -y, --full        Display full disk info\n  -e, --errors      Display only disks with errors / critical temperature\n  -s, --no-header   Suppress header\n  -J, --json        Output as JSON\n```\n\n## Exit codes\n\n* **1** critical temperature\n* **2** errors detected\n\nThe tool considers drive has an errors, if the following S.M.A.R.T. fields are\ngreater than zero:\n\n* End-to-End_Error\n* Seek_Error_Rate\n* Raw_Read_Error_Rate\n* UDMA_CRC_Error_Count", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/alttch/shd", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "shd", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/shd/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/shd/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/alttch/shd"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/shd/0.0.12/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Show HDD/SSD list", "version": "0.0.12", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Show pretty HDD/SSD list</h1>\n<p>Long time ago when I've switched from Solaris to Linux, I missed \"hd\" utility.\nIn Linux \"hd\" command is used for a hex dump, in Solaris it displayed a pretty\ntable with HDD info.</p>\n<p>I wrote \"shd\" shell script with a similar functionality. Now I rewrote it in\nPython, added options and pretty colors, and releasing it to public.</p>\n<img src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/89136db9913814b40714fc4a00dc1b7b9dea40d2/68747470733a2f2f7261772e67697468756275736572636f6e74656e742e636f6d2f616c747463682f7368642f6d61737465722f64656d6f2e676966\">\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install <em>smartmontools</em>, then:</p>\n<pre><code>python3 -m pip install shd\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>Tool should be started under root, to obtain S.M.A.R.T. info</p>\n<pre><code>shd [-h] [--temp-warn TEMP] [--temp-crit TEMP] [-R] [-y] [-e] [-s] [-J]\n\n  --temp-warn TEMP  Warning temperature, default: 40 C\n  --temp-crit TEMP  Critical temperature, default: 45 C\n  --fh, --fahrenheit  Temperature in Fahrenheit\n  -R, --raw         Suppress colors\n  -y, --full        Display full disk info\n  -e, --errors      Display only disks with errors / critical temperature\n  -s, --no-header   Suppress header\n  -J, --json        Output as JSON\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Exit codes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>1</strong> critical temperature</li>\n<li><strong>2</strong> errors detected</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The tool considers drive has an errors, if the following S.M.A.R.T. fields are\ngreater than zero:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>End-to-End_Error</li>\n<li>Seek_Error_Rate</li>\n<li>Raw_Read_Error_Rate</li>\n<li>UDMA_CRC_Error_Count</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6665921, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6109c3b6ce9a45cf8879e15d88144056", "sha256": "35579db65942f8979615b67ac367eb7e04fa789d3aeca9db0662981202d95deb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "shd-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6109c3b6ce9a45cf8879e15d88144056", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3260, "upload_time": "2020-02-20T01:21:31", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-20T01:21:31.846236Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/cb/b6/636a365b338685d1fe2e1aa793e74fa7fde476714c29f5708833b2de9b91/shd-0.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.10": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "dd09954ff108b780f7d523e68dfc1319", "sha256": "64f85249e15721dbb73323f4caf640fbe4b1285c807e9fdd1f88d8c7b12ec267"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "shd-0.0.10.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "dd09954ff108b780f7d523e68dfc1319", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3489, "upload_time": "2020-02-20T03:02:43", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-20T03:02:43.242233Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/61/57/3501ac583df0cb69b327dc911323f96d63ce6c81d5fd129914e2dd07cdc4/shd-0.0.10.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.11": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "dc45b0bf2b6635a907874de821c5a619", "sha256": "9b169a57b64ad97b64a78a5a6cd6415728c8e8a015ab45ce8a03a9a8a8681485"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "shd-0.0.11.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "dc45b0bf2b6635a907874de821c5a619", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3569, "upload_time": "2020-02-20T05:04:18", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-20T05:04:18.767880Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/90/98/53a0a8a858385532aefd80ef4bc3645eb21876d5e912f72765d783b6a3a7/shd-0.0.11.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.12": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "d10dafb9bfffcf45605